<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Squiers</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-09"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 460.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copy of a letter from A. W.
                            Pinkham, of Lynn, Mass., to the Hon. E. W. Roberts, a member of the
                            House of Representatives,<note n="a" xml:id="d274fna">Not
                                printed.</note> regarding the proposed enforcement of a law in Cuba
                            requiring a statement of the formula of patent medicines in order to
                            obtain authorization for their sale.</p>
                        <p>The complainant represents that if the law is enfofced, he will nave to
                            withdraw from the sale of his preparations in Cuba.</p>
                        <p>You may use your good offices in the matter and report to the
                            Department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B.
                            Loomis.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>